4 main data types

    Text fields
Binary field
Numeric fields
AUTO_INCREMENT

    STRING FIELD
*UNDERSTAND CHARACTER SETS AND ARE INDEXABLE FOR SEACHING
*CHAR == allocate the entire space(faster for small strings where lenght is known)
*VARCHAR == allocates a variable amount of space depending on the data lenght(less space)

    TEXT FIELDS
*TINYTEXT UP TO 255 CHARACTERS
*TEXT 65K
*MEDIUMTEXT 16m
*LONGTEXT 4G

*GENERALLY NOT USED WITH INDEXING OR SORTING -and only limited to a prefix

    Binary Types
byte = 8 bits

*Bite(n) up to 255 bytes
VARBINARY(n) up to 65k bytes

small images -data
not indexed or sorted

    Binary Large Objects(BLOB)
*Large raw data, files, images, word documents, PDFs, moveies and ets.
*No translation, indexing, or character set

*TINYBLOB(n) up to 255
*BLOB(n) 65k
*MEDIUMBLOB(n) 16M
*LONGBLOB(n) 4G

    Integer Numbers
Integer numbers are very afficient, take little starage, and easy proces
*TINYINT (-128,128)
*SMALLINT (-32768, 32768)
*INT (2 BILLION)
*BIGINT (10**19 ISH)

    Floating point numbers
Can be represented a wide range of values, but accuracy is limited.
*FLOAT (32 bit) 10**38 7 digits of accuracy
*DOUBLE (64) 10**308 14 digits of accuracy

    DATES
*TIMESTAMP - 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS' (1970,2037)
*DATETIME - 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'
*DATE - 'YYYY-MM-DD'
TIME - 'HH:MM:SS'

Build in MySQL function NOW()